One person died from a heart attack, at least 200 people were injured and extensive damage and landslides occurred along the eastern coast of Hokkaido. Felt strongly in northern Honshu and as far south as the Tokyo area. Tsunami wave heights from selected tide stations (peak-to-trough) were as follows: 346 cm. at Hanasaki, 164 cm. at Kushiro, 26 cm. at Abashiri, Hokkaido; 144 cm. at Miyako, 130 cm. at Hachinohe, 92 cm. at Ofunato, 62 cm. at Onahama, 46 cm. at Omae-zaki, 42 cm. at Choshi, Honshu; 162 cm. on Chichi-shima; 300 cm. at Yuzhno-Kurilsk, Kunashir Island, 15 cm. on Shemya, 16 cm. at Pago Pago, American Samoa, 17 cm. on Wake Island, 50 cm. on Midway Island and 48 cm. at Hilo, Hawaii. Complex event observed on broadband displacement seismograms.
